cs.AR, cs.DB, cs.OS, cs.DC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper discusses the architecture and performance of a new type of memory module, which could fall under this category.
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper explores the performance of the Optane DC PMM in the context of file systems and database applications.
- cs.OS (Operating Systems): The paper discusses the use of Optane DC PMMs as persistent memory in user-space applications, which could fall under this category.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper explores the performance of Optane DC PMMs in various modes and scenarios, which could fall under this category.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the performance of Optane DC PMMs in the context of system-level applications, which could fall under this category.
